# Git Commit Policy

NEVER run `git commit`, `git push`, or any destructive git command unless the user **explicitly** asks you to commit or push in that message.

- Writing and editing code is fine — do it freely.
- Staging files (`git add`) is fine as preparation when asked to commit.
- But do NOT commit or push on your own as a side-effect of fixing a bug or implementing a feature.

## When the user asks to commit

Ask for confirmation of the commit message if unclear. Use the `-m` flag always:

```bash
git commit -m "your message here"
```

Never open an interactive editor for commits.
